commentable_entity.title: Unban Scorpione on DGG
commentable_entity.description:
Sometimes mistakes are made. Sometimes good people can be seen as bad people just because they cringe and socially stupid.

It was months since respected member of our community was banned. His friends are no longer seeing him in chat and that's really sad.

I (a woman) believe Scorp was wrongly banned. Yes, he might been cringe and toxic, but he did not harassed anyone. The only case that was public included a grown ass woman who was dming with him for a long time and was perfectly fine. She later showed some of their DMs to her friends. These friends did not liked Scorp so they said it was sexual harassment. Said woman did not felt harrased before and was claiming in gen chat that Scorp is her friend after alleged harassment. 

 

Even thought I take the issue of gendered violence seriously (i support Amber Heard btw), i think in this particular case there was no violence. As one of the most talented ppl of our generation said: "hahaha how the fuck cyber bullying real just walk away from the screen". In our case, ladies, just block ppl if u dont wanna talk with them. I do it all the time.

 

In conclusion: Scorp promised me that he'll be no longer DM'ing women. I believe in second chances and i believe in that man. Let the memes live.

Glory to DGG #freescorp

P.S. Scorp did NOT actually wanted to pee on that woman "to mark his territory" it was just a joke
